); Antennal segment II not produced laterally, almost symmetrical (
<figureCitation box="[1342,1423,1632,1655]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 11" captionStartId="3.[151,258,824,846]" captionTargetBox="[168,1424,196,803]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[156,1430,191,803]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 11. Oelschlaegera ferdowsii Male: (9) Adult (10) Head, antenna and fore leg (10) Abdominal sternites III – VI." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/262685/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="297">
